EENG 4317 - Power Electronics Design and Applications
The use of solid state components in power systems; rectifying devices;
diode circuits and rectifiers; controlled rectifier circuits; AC voltage
controllers; thyristor commutation techniques; DC choppers; speedtorque
characteristics of motors and loads; starting, braking and transient
analysis of electric motors; introduction to HVDC. Three hours of lecture
per week.
Prerequisite: EENG 4309. Prerequisite or Corequisite: EENG 4310.
